metadata.name: Labyrinth #167
metadata.description:
The beginning of life is an incessant dream, a kaleidoscope of surprising discoveries, a colorful labyrinth in which you are enclosed by indefinitely high walls or a void, which you have to pass on your own. The person who may later become a guide through the labyrinth is still hiding behind some wall, past another turn. The main goal is to find him. If you succeed...


But you will succeed.


© Victoria Crux, 2022

metadata.name: Citta #126
metadata.description:
Citta as mind Citta as city. 

Citta is city of interconnected minds from future of Metropolis IX(Project id:13292), after singularity people uploaded their consciousness into inorganic self-constructing structures. 

There are 13 different mind-hives named with upper case letters, only "MC-00001" is monochrome rest is in color. "SCMB" and "SCCB' are in spiral formation due to their nature.

Press 1 to 8 export PNG 1000px to 8000px 
9 exports 10000px PNG 

Exports are dependent on CPU, so larger export might take time. Please be patient. If you cannot export reach me out.

Works best in Chrome browser. 

Created with p5.js and canvas api.
Murat Atimtay 2022 | @atimtay | www.muratatimtay.com

metadata.name: Vertical World #94
metadata.description:
This artwork is a kind of my inquiry about ambiguous boundaries.
I was a child who liked to draw but always been dissatisfied with my work. Now through coding, I was able to create the "feelings" that I wanted to express. This work is not to imitate a certain landscape or painting style, but simply paint with different brushes, and cooperate with the randomness of the computer.
"I" creates horizontal order, and "computer" creates vertical disorder. My intention is to create
ambiguous visuals in a way that doesn't give specific images, but vague atmosphere.
The meaning is computer-generated and positioned through your eyes.
(It may take more time to render if you using Firefox browser.)

- Press [s] to save png image

Created by haxenfan using p5js.

metadata.name: Chromatic Waves #17
metadata.description:
Threads of color are weaved together, interacting and vibrating.

SVG generated with JavaScript.

The SVG can be saved by pressing "s" on the full-screen view.
A PNG version can be exported by pressing "e" on the full-screen view.

By default the dimensions of the export are 3200×2400.
These dimensions can be changed by adding, for example, ?w=3200&h=1800 to the full-screen page URL, where w is the desired width and h the desired height. Then press "e" to export at this size.

metadata.name: Paper Art 3D #104
metadata.description:
Welcome to “Paper Art 3D”

“Paper Art 3D” is the beginning of my journey as a new generative art creator. Starting from simple geometrical shapes like a small step towards to something greater in the future. 
It all began from simple 3D shapes that combined into mountains, trees, and houses. Then everything expanded and united into many exotic cityscapes. Each with their own style and uniqueness.

Built with three.js.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - -
Space Bar  --> Save a simple screenshot image of the canvas
Mouse: Drag & Scroll  --> Rotate & Zoom in-out 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - -
